---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Terms of Use',
  url: 'https://purplepeaksapps.com/terms',
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | Purple Peaks Apps"
  description="Terms governing your use of the Purple Peaks Apps website and software products."
  path="/terms"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 15, 2026</p>
      <p class="reviewed">Last reviewed: July 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of purplepeaksapps.com (the
        "Site") and any software applications made available by Purple Peaks Apps LLC, including
        the PSG Partner Portal (collectively, the "Services"). By accessing or using the Site or
        Services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use
        the Site or Services.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Description of Services</h2>
      <p>
        Purple Peaks Apps LLC develops and provides software tools for insurance professionals.
        The Site provides general information about these tools; access to and use of any
        specific application (such as the PSG Partner Portal) may be subject to additional
        product-specific terms, license agreements, or account requirements provided to you
        separately.
      </p>

      <h2>2. No Warranty; "As Is" Basis</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and Services are provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without
        warranties of any kind, whether express, implied, or statutory, including but not limited
        to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
        non-infringement, or uninterrupted or error-free operation. We do not warrant that the
        Site or Services will meet your requirements, be available at any particular time, or be
        free of defects, bugs, or security vulnerabilities.
      </p>

      <h2>3. No Guarantee of Results</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on the Site constitutes a guarantee of any particular business outcome, cost
        savings, efficiency gain, or performance result from using our software products. Any
        descriptions of product features or benefits are general in nature and may vary based on
        your specific use case, configuration, and environment.
      </p>

      <h2>4. No Guarantee of Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        Software features, pricing, and availability change over time. While we strive to keep
        this Site accurate and current, we make no warranty, express or implied, that any
        information on the Site is complete, accurate, or up to date. Always confirm current
        product details directly with Purple Peaks Apps LLC before making a purchasing or
        implementation decision.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Use of the Site and Services</h2>
      <p>
        You agree to use the Site and Services only for lawful purposes and in a manner
        consistent with these Terms. You may not: (a) copy, reproduce, reverse-engineer, or
        redistribute Site content or Service software without our written permission; (b)
        attempt to interfere with the normal operation or security of the Site or Services; or
        (c) submit false or misleading information through any form on the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content and software on the Site, including text, graphics, logos, and application
        code, is owned by or licensed to Purple Peaks Apps LLC and is protected by applicable
        intellectual property laws. Except as expressly authorized (such as under a separate
        license agreement for a specific product), you may not copy, modify, distribute, sell, or
        lease any part of the Site or Services.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Third-Party Links and Integrations</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and Services may link to or integrate with third-party websites, tools, or
        platforms for your convenience. We do not control and are not responsible for the
        content, availability, or practices of third-party sites or services.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Purple Peaks Apps LLC shall not be liable for any
        direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of
        or related to your use of, or inability to use, the Site or Services, including any
        business decisions made based on information found on the Site, even if we have been
        advised of the possibility of such damages.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Communications Consent</h2>
      <p>
        By submitting a form on this Site, you consent to be contacted as described in our{' '}
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>, including by phone, text, and email, regarding
        your inquiry and related products and services.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise these Terms from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects the
        most recent revision. Continued use of the Site or Services after changes are posted
        constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of North Carolina, without regard to
        its conflict of law principles.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms may be directed to Purple Peaks Apps LLC through our{' '}
        <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .eyebrow { color: var(--color-teal); }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .reviewed { color: #b6a4cb; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.25rem; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
